\v 14 And they went vp into the citie: \add and\add* when they were come into the citie, behold, Samuel came out against them, for to goe vp to the hie place.
\v 15 ¶ \x + \xo 9:15 \xt Chap. 15.1. acts. 13.21.\x*Now the \nd LORD\nd* had \f + \fr 9:15 \ft Heb. reveiled the eare of Samuel.\f*told Samuel in his eare a day before Saul came, saying,
\v 16 To morrow about this time I will send thee a man out of the land of Beniamin, and thou shalt anoynt him \add to be\add* Captaine ouer my people Israel, that he may saue my people out of the hand of the Philistines: for I haue looked vpon my people, because their cry is come vnto me.
\v 17 And when Samuel saw Saul, the \nd LORD\nd* said vnto him, Behold the man whom I spake to thee of: this same shall \f + \fr 9:17 \ft Hebr. restraine in.\f*reigne ouer my people.
\v 18 Then Saul drew neere to Samuel in the gate, and said, Tell me, I pray thee, where the Seers house \add is\add*.
\v 19 And Samuel answered Saul, and said, I \add am\add* the Seer: Goe vp before me vnto the high place, for ye shall eate with me to day, and to morrow I will let thee goe, and will tell thee all that \add is\add* in thine heart.
\v 20 And as for thine asses that were lost \f + \fr 9:20 \ft Hebr. to day three dayes.\f*three dayes agoe, set not thy minde on them, for they are found: And on whom is all the desire of Israel? is it not on thee, & on all thy fathers house?
\v 21 And Saul answered, and said, \add Am\add* not I a Beniamite, of the smallest of the tribes of Israel? and my family the least of all the families of the tribe of Beniamin? Wherefore then speakest thou \f + \fr 9:21 \ft Hebr. according to this word?\f*so to me?
