\v 23 And Samuel said vnto the cooke, Bring the portion which I gaue thee, of which I said vnto thee, Set it by thee.
\v 24 And the cooke took vp the shoulder, and \add that\add* which \add was\add* vpon \add it\add*, and set it before Saul, and \add Samuel\add* said, Behold, that which is \f + \fr 9:24 \ft Or, reserued.\f*left, set \add it\add* before thee, \add and\add* eate: for vnto this time hath it bene kept for thee, since I said I haue inuited the people: So Saul did eat with Samuel that day.
\v 25 ¶ And when they were come downe from the high place into the citie, \add Samuel\add* communed with Saul vpon the top of the house.
\v 26 And they arose early: and it came to passe about the spring of the day, that Samuel called Saul to the top of the house, saying, Up, that I may send thee away: And Saul arose, and they went out both of them, hee and Samuel, abroad.
\v 27 \add And\add* as they were going downe to the end of the city, Samuel said to Saul, Bid the seruant passe on before vs, (and he passed on) but stand thou still \f + \fr 9:27 \ft Hebr. to day.\f*a while, that I may shew thee the word of God.
\c 10
\iex 1 Samuel anoynteth Saul. 2 Hee confirmeth him by prediction of three signes. 9 Sauls heart is changed, and he prophecieth. 14 He concealeth the matter of the kingdome from his vncle. 17 Saul is chosen at Mizpeh by lot. 26 The different affections of his subiects.
\v 1 ¶ Then Samuel tooke a viall of oile, and powred \add it\add* vpon his head, & kissed him, and said, \add Is it\add* not because the \nd LORD\nd* hath anoynted thee \add to be\add* captain ouer his inheritance?
\v 2 When thou art departed from me to day, then thou shalt find two men by \x + \xo 10:2 \xt Gen. 35.20.\x*Rachels sepulchre in the border of Beniamin, at Zelzah: and they will say vnto thee, The asses which thou wentest to seeke, are found: and loe, thy father hath left \f + \fr 10:2 \ft Heb. the businesse.\f*the care of the asses, and sorroweth for you, saying, What shall I doe for my sonne?
