\v 9 ¶ And it was \add so\add* that when he had turned his \f + \fr 10:9 \ft Heb. shoulder.\f*backe to go from Samuel, God \f + \fr 10:9 \ft Heb. turned.\f*gaue him another heart: and all those signes came to passe that day.
\v 10 And when they came thither to the hill, behold, a company of the prophets met him, and the spirit of God came vpon him, and hee prophesied among them.
\v 11 And it came to passe when all that knew him beforetime, saw, that behold, hee prophesied among the prophets, then the people said \f + \fr 10:11 \ft Heb. A man to his neighbour.\f*one to another, What is this that is come vnto the sonne of Kish? \x + \xo 10:11 \xt Chap. 19.24.\x*Is Saul also among the prophets?
